channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: NEW: In 2021 9/11 Speech, Tim Walz References 'Being on the Tarmac at Bagram' During a Ramp Ceremony
Trump legal cases in limbo after SCOTUS immunity ruling, freeing up schedule to campaign
item.description: Former President Trump has had a number of legal victories in recent weeks, putting a pause on a majority of cases and delaying others that could have complicated his campaigning during the general election season.

item.title: Biden Tackles Helpline Wait Times in Pro-Consumer Push
item.description: The Biden administration Monday unveiled new rules and efforts targeting consumer annoyances ranging from hard-to-cancel subscriptions, cumbersome insurance forms, and not being able to get a live customer service agent on the phone.

item.title: Pelosi Dons Tinfoil Hat, Suggests Biden Didn't Write That July Letter Claiming He Was Staying in Race
Here's where the vice presidential candidates stand on top issues
item.description: Republican Sen. JD Vance and Democratic Gov. Tim Walz have differing views on most key issues as they campaign against one another as the 2024 vice presidential nominees.

item.title: Jerusalem Post Editor: Harris Poses Existential Threat to Israel
item.description: If Vice President Kamala Harris gets elected in November, it would spell an existential threat to Israel, The Jerusalem Post editor-in-chief Zvika Klein wrote Friday.

item.title: Former Battalion Commander Lights Up Tim Walz Over Stolen Valor Scandal—'He Did Not Earn the Rank'
Harris hauls in $12 million at San Francisco fundraiser as Pelosi welcomes vice president home
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris hauls in over $12 million in her race against Donald Trump, at a fundraiser in San Francisco where she was introduced by former House Speaker Nancy Pelosi

item.title: Rep. Bryan Steil to Newsmax: Probe ActBlue for 'Potential Money-Laundering Scheme'
item.description: Rep. Bryan Steil, R-Wis., has urged the Federal Election Commission (FEC) to enact emergency rule making in order to ensure compliance with campaign finance laws and prevent fraud.

item.title: Auburn University Fisheries Facility Helps Farmers Plagued by Oversized Fish
Biden to hit campaign trail for Harris in Pennsylvania
item.description: President Biden said in a CBS interview that he will be hitting the campaign trail in Pennsylvania in support of Vice President Harris' presidential run.

item.title: Dave McCormick Criticizes Harris Over Supporting Fracking Ban
item.description: Dave McCormick, the challenger to Sen. Bob Casey, D-Pa., blasted Vice President Kamala Harris for changing her position on fracking after becoming the Democrat nominee for president.

item.title: Nailed It: Butler, PA Artist Recreates Iconic, Trump Post-Assassination Attempt Moment With Hardware
Secret Service hints it wasn’t behind salon break-in during Kamala Harris campaign event
item.description: The U.S. Secret Service on Sunday hinted it wasn't involved in a break-in of a hair salon during a Kamala Harris campaign event in Massachusetts late last month.

item.title: Sen. Cotton: Harris 'Naive' on Iran, Not Tough on Hamas
item.description: Sen. Tom Cotton on Sunday harshly criticized Vice President Kamala Harris as both "naive" on Tehran and soft on Hamas. The Arkansas Republican told "Fox News Sunday" that the policy of the Democrat presidential candidate toward Israel since the Oct. 7 massacre by Hamas...
